    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="gez">            
               <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="Introduction">
                <label>Introduction</label>
                   <ab>
                     በስመ፡ አብ፡<gap reason="ellipsis"/> ንጽሕፍ፡ እንከ፡ ድርሳነ፡ ተዝካረ፡ መድኃኒነ፡
                     ዘይትነበብ፡ ለለወርኁ፡ በገጸ፡ ኵሉ፡ መካን፡ በቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፨ ዘከሠተ፡ ሎቱ፡ ለመባዓ፡
                      ጽዮን፡ ለምክንያተ፡ ድኂን፡ ዘተውህቦሙ፡
                      ለአማንያን፡ ወዕብነ፡ ዕቅፍት፡ ለከሐድያን፡ ዘያከብሮ፡
                      ለዝንቱ፡ በዓል፡ በኃይለ፡ መስቀሉ፡ ይዕቀቦ፡ ለይኩን፡
                   </ab>
                   <note>After <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy024"/>.</note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="SwollenThroat">
                   <label>How the saint healed a child with a swollen throat</label>
                   <ab>
                     <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ወመጽአት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ጸዊራ፡ ሕፃነ፡ ሕሙመ፡ ዘሐብጠ፡ ጕርኤሁ፡ ዘኢይክል፡
                     ጥቢወ፡ ጥባ፡ ለእሙ። ወትቤሎ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ነጽር፡ አባ፡ እስመ፡ ይመውት፡ ወልድየ፡ ወፈውሶ፡ ሊተ፡
                     ተማኅፀንኩ፡ በአምላክከ። ወይቤላ፡ ለእመ፡ ተፈወሰ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ሕፃን፡ ትሁቢዮኑ፡ ብጽዓተ፡
                     ከመ፡ ይግበር፡ ለተዝካረ፡ መድኅን። ወትቤሎ፡ እወ፡ ይኩን፡ በከመ፡ ትቤ።
                   </ab>
                   <note>After <bibl><ptr target="bm:Budge1898MabaaSeyon"/><citedRange unit="page">16-17</citedRange></bibl>,
                    cp. <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy024"/>, no. 2-1 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>.</note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="SickChild">
                  <label>How the saint healed a sick child brought to the saint by his mother</label>
                  <ab>
                    <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ወካዕበ፡ መጽአት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ጽዊራ፡ ሕፃነ፡ ሕሙመ፡ ዘአልጸቀ፡ ለመዊት። ወገደፈቶ፡ ታሕተ፡
                    እገሪሁ። ወትቤሎ፡ ንሣእ፡ ዘነተ፡ ሕፃነ፡ ለእመ፡ ፈወስኮ፡ በጸሎትከ፡ ቅድስት፡ ይኩንከ፡ ገብረ። ወይቤላ፡ ሊተሰ፡ ኢይኩነኒ፡ አላ፡ ይኩን፡ ገብሮ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ።
                  </ab>
                   <note>After <bibl><ptr target="bm:Budge1898MabaaSeyon"/><citedRange unit="page">17-18</citedRange></bibl>,
                 cp. <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy024"/>, no. 2-2 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>.</note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="LightDough">
                   <label>Light that appeared over the dough
                     from which the bread for the commemoration of the Saviour of the World was made</label>
                   <ab>
                     <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ወሀሎ፡ በአስፈሬዳ፡ ምሉእ፡ ሐሪፅ፡ ዘይትገበር፡ ለኅብስተ፡ ተዝካሩ፡
                     ለወልደ፡ እግዚአብሔር፤ እግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፤ ኮነ፡ በላዕሌሁ፡ ለሐሪጽ፡ ጽቃውዕኒ፡ ይነድድ፡ እሳት፡ ዘያንጸበርቅ፡ ፈድፋደ።
                   </ab>
                   <note>After <bibl><ptr target="bm:Budge1898MabaaSeyon"/><citedRange unit="page">18</citedRange></bibl>, cp.
                   <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy024"/>, cp. no. 4c in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML1779"/>.
                   </note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="Sterile">
                   <label>The barren woman who could bear children by the prayer of the saint</label>
                   <ab>
                     <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ወመጽአ፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ ወትቤሎ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡ ተዘክረኒ፡ በጸሎትከ፡ ቅድስት፤ እስመ፡ በጻሕኩ፡
                     ኀበ፡ ብዙሐን፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ወኢፈጸምኩ፡ ጻሕቅየ።
                   </ab>
                   <note>After
                   <bibl><ptr target="bm:Budge1898MabaaSeyon"/><citedRange unit="page">18</citedRange></bibl>, cp. no. 2-4 in
                  <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML4817"/>.
                   </note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="BreadIcon">
                  <label>Pieces of bread for the commemoration of the Saviour of the
                    World turned into an icon of the Virgin Mary</label>
                  <ab>
                  <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ብእሲት፡ እምነ፡ አሐቲሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡ ወሰአለቶ፡ ከመ፡
                  የሀባ፡ እምኅብስተ፡ ተዝካሩ፡ ለመድኃኒነ። ወወሀባ፡ ፪ፍርፋራተ፡ ወነሢአ፡ ዘንተ፡ እንዘ፡ ተሐውር፡ ረከባ፡ ፩መነኮስ፡ ወሰአላ፡ ከመ፡ ተሀቦ፡ ውእተ፡ ፍርፋራተ፡
                    </ab>
                    <note>After <bibl><ptr target="bm:Budge1898MabaaSeyon"/><citedRange unit="page">19</citedRange></bibl>, cp.
                     <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy024"/>, no. 2-2-5 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML4817"/>.
                    </note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="AnotherBread">
                  <label>The man who ate the bread for the commemoration of the Saviour
                    of the World after he ate another bread</label>
                  <ab>
                  <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ወአሐተ፡ ዕለተ፡ እንዘ፡ ይሁቦሙ፡ በእደዊሁ፡ እምውእቱ፡ ኅብስት፡
                  በከመ፡ ይሁቦሙ፡ ዘልፈ፡ እምድኅረ፡ ቍርባን፡ አቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡ ተመጠወ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡
                  እምድኅረ፡ በልዩ፡ ካልአ፡ ኀብስተ። ወኢያእመሮ፡ መኑሂ፡ ዘከመ፡ ገብረ፡ ዘንተ፡ </ab>
                    <note>After <bibl><ptr target="bm:Budge1898MabaaSeyon"/><citedRange unit="page">19-20</citedRange></bibl>,
                     no. 2-3 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>, no. 2-2-6 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML4817"/>.</note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="Devotion">
                  <label>Devotion of ʾabuna Takla Māryām to the celebration of the commemoration of the Saviour</label>
                  <ab>
                    <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ስምዑ፡ አበውየ፡ ወአኀውየ፡ እለ፡ ታፈቅረዎ፡ ለክርስቶስ፡ ዕበያ፡ ተአምሪሁ፡<gap reason="ellipsis"/> ወብፁዕ፡
                    አቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡ ያፈቅሮ፡ ለመድኀኒነ፡ ወኢይዴምር፡ ምስለ፡ ካልአን፡ በዓላት፡ መባዓ ወዕጣነ፡ ቅብዓ፡
                    </ab>
                    <note>After no. 2-4 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>,
                    probably <bibl><ptr target="bm:Budge1898MabaaSeyon"/><citedRange unit="page">20</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="Reward">
                  <label>Reward for those who observe the commemoration of the Saviour of the World</label>
                  <ab>
                    <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ስምዑ፡ ዘይቤ፡ መድኅን፡ ዘገብረ፡ ተዝካርየ፡ በኅብስት፡ ወበስዋዐ፡ አው፡ ዘይሁብ፡
                    ማኅቶተ፡ ለቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ እማዕምቀ፡ ልቡ፡ስሒቆ፡ ተዘኪሮ፡ ስቅለትየ፡
                     አማን፡ አብለክመ፡
                    </ab>
                      <note>After no. 2-5 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>.</note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="SoulsHell">
                  <label>How the saint brought many souls from Hell by the order of the Child Jesus</label>
                  <ab>
                    <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ወካዕበ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ዕለት፡ እንዘ፡ ይጸሊ፡ ቀዊሞ፡ በጽሒቅ፡ አቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡
                    ርእየ፡ ሕፃነ፡ እምርሑቅ፡ እንዘ፡ ይትዋነይ፡ አምሳለ፡ ሕፃናት፡ እኂዞ፡ በትረ፡ ወርቅ፡
                    </ab>
                  <note>After no. 2-6 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>.</note>
                </div>

                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="ChildJesus">
                  <label>How the Child Jesus appeared to the saint who was going to Warwar to celebrate
                    the feast of Masqal Kǝbrā</label>
                  <ab>
                    <gap reason="ellipsis"/>ወእምዝ፡ ሖረ፡ አቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡ ሀገረ፡ ዳሞት፡ ኀበ፡ ተዝካረ፡ መስቀል፡ ክብራ፡ ብፅዕት፡ በቃሉ፡
                    ይቤ፡ ለሊሁ፡ እንዘ፡ አሐውር፡ በፍኖት፡ ርኢኩ፡ ሰብአ፡ ብዙኀነ፡ ብምሥያጥ፡ ዘወርወር፡
                    </ab>
                    <note>After no. 2-7 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>.</note>
                </div>


                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="Gafat">
                  <label>The promise of the Lord to convert Gāfāt and give them to Mabāʾa Ṣǝyon</label>
                  <ab>
                  </ab>
                  <note>After no. 2-8 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>.</note>
                  </div>

                    <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="VisionHeaven">
                    <label>Vision of Takla Māryām about the lives of the saints in Heaven</label>
                    <ab>
                    </ab>
                    <note>After no. 2-9 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3420"/>.</note>
                    </div>


                  <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="ThrowingBread">
                  <label>The man who threw down the bread of the memorial feast because of bad temper</label>
                  <ab>
                  </ab>
                  <note>No. 2-2-7 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML4817"/>.</note>
                  </div>

                  <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="Seclusion">
                    <label>How Takla Ḥawāryāt went into seclusion until the Lord revealed to him the memorial day of his death</label>
                    <ab>
                    </ab>
                    <note>No. 2-2-8 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML4817"/>.</note>
                    </div>


                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="Warab">
                  <label>The monastic community in Qolozǝyā (Warab) which decided to observe the memorial day of the Saviour</label>
                    <ab>
                    </ab>
                    <note>No. 2-2-9 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML4817"/>.</note>
                  </div>

                  <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="ServantWife">
                    <label>How the servant, who was serving at the memorial feast of the Saviour, became sick because he
                    had slept with his wife the previous night</label>
                      <ab>
                      </ab>
                      <note>No. 2-2-10 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML4817"/>.</note>
                    </div>

                    <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:id="WomanKite">
                      <label>The story of the woman from Dārāt whose rooster was carried off by a kite</label>
                        <ab>
                        </ab>
                        <note>No. 2-2-11 in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML4817"/>.</note>
                      </div>
</div>
